   "body" : "Remove a circular dependency - this would remove the one in #22675 as well.\r\n\r\nNot 100% sure if this is the right approach, but here's my reasoning: validation should depend on txmempool (e.g. `CChainstateManager` has a mempool and we often need to know what's in our mempool to validate transactions), but txmempool is a data structure that shouldn't really need to know state. The two places where txmempool currently needs validation are in `check()` and `removeForReorg`. This PR moves some stuff to `CChainState` (i.e. when we need to check against the coins cache, grab block height, etc.) and keeps some stuff in `CTxMemPool` (i.e. when we need access to private data).",
